article.headline: IPFW 67, North Florida 61
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- David Carson scored 16 points and Indiana University-Purdue Fort Wayne defeated North Florida 67-61 on Sunday. Carson led four IPFW players in double figures as Nick Daniels tallied 14 points and Zach Plackemeier and Deilvez Yearby had 12 each. Daniels was a perfect 4-for-4 form beyond the 3-point arc to lead the Mastadons (5-8) to a 50 percent 3-point performance (7 of 14). IPFW also shot 50 percent (21 of 42) from the floor, compared to 37 percent (19 of 51) by the Ospreys (2-9). Germaine Sparkes scored 13 points as North Florida's only players in double figures. North Florida outrebounded IPFW 34-25 with DeVon Jones and Cortez Riley grabbing six each.
